The reduction of the sugar cane industry was an economic necessity: the 155 sugar cane factories were technically outdated and hardly competitive for the country.
The initial idea was to concentrate production on the most efficient factories, the annual production objective was 4 million tons.
They left only the factories that can produce sugar for a maximum of 4 Centavos (0.03 euros).
The solution to unemployment?
The motives which led to such measures were the low productivity of sugar cane plantations and the sugar crisis on the world market.
