From 2017 to 2025, the price of unrefined sugar must remain between 15 and 16 cent per pound, according to the 2016 Report "Agricultural Prospectives" by the OECD and FAO, the United Nations Agricultural and Food Organisation.
If the current production would reach the level of 2001 (3.6 million tonnes), the raw sugar exports would generate about 85 million dollars for the country.
