Young people from the First Nations communities all over Canada concern themselves with themes that are important to them. they do so using Hip-Hop, thanks to a series of hiking workshops.
As part of the N'we Jinan-Tour, since 2014 workshop leaders bring mobile audio studios directly to schools and youth centres to teach youth groups songwriting, recording, audio and video production and live performances.
