A blog with the name untranslatable (e.g. unremovable) endeavours to provide language enthusiasts with a selection of words from all over the world that are difficult or not at all to translate.
There are such words in every language: they express certain situations or feelings which are often very complex or specific.
Some of these irreplaceable words are already well known today (like the famous Portuguese saudade) and others deeply rooted in a special culture (e.g. the Spanish Sobremesa).
