Clenora Hudson-Weems, author of the book Africana womanism: recall (example: Africa-Womanismus: as we recapture ourselves), we can defend ourselves by defining ourselves in our own way. and not only that - black women can also create spaces in which they are completely safe and in which the cultural, mental, emotional, physical and even the spiritual elements can be worshipped who make up the black woman.
