The authorities systematically restrict peaceful and legitimate activities in the field of human rights and prevent citizens, including activists from expressing their views on the country's public affairs, such as corruption in authorities and institutions, both online and offline.
The attack on Azamn, its closure and imprisonment three of its editors last year is a hard blow to press freedom in the country.
Azamn is an independent newspaper reported since its foundation in 2007 on Corruption in Oman (an absolute monarchy) until it was banned by the authorities in August 2016.
